create table api_keys (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description varchar(500),
        expires_at timestamp(6),
        key_hash varchar(64) not null,
        last_used_at timestamp(6),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        prefix varchar(16) not null,
        rate_limit integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table asset_assignments (
        asset_id bigint not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (asset_id, user_id)
    )

create table assets (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        asset_tag varchar(50) not null,
        brand varchar(100),
        condition enum ('BROKEN','EXCELLENT','FAIR','GOOD','POOR') not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        location varchar(100),
        model varchar(100),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance date,
        notes TEXT,
        purchase_date date,
        purchase_price numeric(10,2),
        serial_number varchar(100),
        status enum ('ASSIGNED','AVAILABLE','DAMAGED','IN_MAINTENANCE','LOST','RETIRED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        warranty_expiry date,
        category_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table categories (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        color_code varchar(50),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        icon varchar(50),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        sort_order integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table invoices (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        amount_due numeric(10,2),
        amount_paid numeric(10,2),
        billing_reason varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        currency varchar(255),
        due_date timestamp(6),
        hosted_invoice_url varchar(255),
        invoice_pdf_url varchar(255),
        paid_at timestamp(6),
        period_end timestamp(6),
        period_start timestamp(6),
        status enum ('DRAFT','OPEN','PAID','UNCOLLECTIBLE','VOID') not null,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_invoice_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_subscription_id varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table maintenance_records (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        completed_date date,
        cost numeric(10,2),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT not null,
        downtime_hours integer,
        maintenance_date date not null,
        maintenance_type varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance_date date,
        notes TEXT,
        parts_used TEXT,
        performed_by varchar(100),
        priority enum ('CRITICAL','HIGH','LOW','MEDIUM','URGENT') not null,
        status enum ('CANCELLED','COMPLETED','IN_PROGRESS','OVERDUE','SCHEDULED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        asset_id bigint not null,
        created_by_user_id bigint,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table payment_methods (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        billing_email varchar(255),
        billing_name varchar(255),
        card_brand varchar(255),
        card_exp_month integer,
        card_exp_year integer,
        card_last4 varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        is_default boolean,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_payment_method_id varchar(255) not null,
        type varchar(255) not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table refresh_tokens (
        id uuid not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) with time zone not null,

        revoked_at timestamp(6) with time zone,
        token_hash varchar(64) not null,
        user_agent varchar(255),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table api_keys (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description varchar(500),
        expires_at timestamp(6),
        key_hash varchar(64) not null,
        last_used_at timestamp(6),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        prefix varchar(16) not null,
        rate_limit integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table asset_assignments (
        asset_id bigint not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (asset_id, user_id)
    )

create table assets (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        asset_tag varchar(50) not null,
        brand varchar(100),
        condition enum ('BROKEN','EXCELLENT','FAIR','GOOD','POOR') not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        location varchar(100),
        model varchar(100),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance date,
        notes TEXT,
        purchase_date date,
        purchase_price numeric(10,2),
        serial_number varchar(100),
        status enum ('ASSIGNED','AVAILABLE','DAMAGED','IN_MAINTENANCE','LOST','RETIRED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        warranty_expiry date,
        category_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table categories (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        color_code varchar(50),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        icon varchar(50),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        sort_order integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table invoices (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        amount_due numeric(10,2),
        amount_paid numeric(10,2),
        billing_reason varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        currency varchar(255),
        due_date timestamp(6),
        hosted_invoice_url varchar(255),
        invoice_pdf_url varchar(255),
        paid_at timestamp(6),
        period_end timestamp(6),
        period_start timestamp(6),
        status enum ('DRAFT','OPEN','PAID','UNCOLLECTIBLE','VOID') not null,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_invoice_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_subscription_id varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table maintenance_records (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        completed_date date,
        cost numeric(10,2),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT not null,
        downtime_hours integer,
        maintenance_date date not null,
        maintenance_type varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance_date date,
        notes TEXT,
        parts_used TEXT,
        performed_by varchar(100),
        priority enum ('CRITICAL','HIGH','LOW','MEDIUM','URGENT') not null,
        status enum ('CANCELLED','COMPLETED','IN_PROGRESS','OVERDUE','SCHEDULED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        asset_id bigint not null,
        created_by_user_id bigint,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table payment_methods (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        billing_email varchar(255),
        billing_name varchar(255),
        card_brand varchar(255),
        card_exp_month integer,
        card_exp_year integer,
        card_last4 varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        is_default boolean,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_payment_method_id varchar(255) not null,
        type varchar(255) not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table refresh_tokens (
        id uuid not null,

        user_agent varchar(255),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table api_keys (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description varchar(500),
        expires_at timestamp(6),
        key_hash varchar(64) not null,
        last_used_at timestamp(6),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        prefix varchar(16) not null,
        rate_limit integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table asset_assignments (
        asset_id bigint not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (asset_id, user_id)
    )

create table assets (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        asset_tag varchar(50) not null,
        brand varchar(100),
        condition enum ('BROKEN','EXCELLENT','FAIR','GOOD','POOR') not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        location varchar(100),
        model varchar(100),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance date,
        notes TEXT,
        purchase_date date,
        purchase_price numeric(10,2),
        serial_number varchar(100),
        status enum ('ASSIGNED','AVAILABLE','DAMAGED','IN_MAINTENANCE','LOST','RETIRED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        warranty_expiry date,
        category_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table categories (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        color_code varchar(50),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        icon varchar(50),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        sort_order integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table invoices (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        amount_due numeric(10,2),
        amount_paid numeric(10,2),
        billing_reason varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        currency varchar(255),
        due_date timestamp(6),
        hosted_invoice_url varchar(255),
        invoice_pdf_url varchar(255),
        paid_at timestamp(6),
        period_end timestamp(6),
        period_start timestamp(6),
        status enum ('DRAFT','OPEN','PAID','UNCOLLECTIBLE','VOID') not null,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_invoice_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_subscription_id varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table maintenance_records (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        completed_date date,
        cost numeric(10,2),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT not null,
        downtime_hours integer,
        maintenance_date date not null,
        maintenance_type varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance_date date,
        notes TEXT,
        parts_used TEXT,
        performed_by varchar(100),
        priority enum ('CRITICAL','HIGH','LOW','MEDIUM','URGENT') not null,
        status enum ('CANCELLED','COMPLETED','IN_PROGRESS','OVERDUE','SCHEDULED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        asset_id bigint not null,
        created_by_user_id bigint,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table payment_methods (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        billing_email varchar(255),
        billing_name varchar(255),
        card_brand varchar(255),
        card_exp_month integer,
        card_exp_year integer,

        stripe_payment_method_id varchar(255) not null,
        type varchar(255) not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table api_keys (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description varchar(500),
        expires_at timestamp(6),
        key_hash varchar(64) not null,
        last_used_at timestamp(6),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        prefix varchar(16) not null,
        rate_limit integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table asset_assignments (
        asset_id bigint not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (asset_id, user_id)
    )

create table assets (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        asset_tag varchar(50) not null,
        brand varchar(100),
        condition_rating enum ('BROKEN','EXCELLENT','FAIR','GOOD','POOR') not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        location varchar(100),
        model varchar(100),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance date,
        notes TEXT,
        purchase_date date,
        purchase_price numeric(10,2),
        serial_number varchar(100),
        status enum ('ASSIGNED','AVAILABLE','DAMAGED','IN_MAINTENANCE','LOST','RETIRED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        warranty_expiry date,
        category_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table categories (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        color_code varchar(50),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,

        icon varchar(50),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        sort_order integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_invoice_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_subscription_id varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        completed_date date,
        cost numeric(10,2),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,

        vendor varchar(100),

        primary key (id)

create table api_keys (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description varchar(500),
        expires_at timestamp(6),
        key_hash varchar(64) not null,
        last_used_at timestamp(6),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        prefix varchar(16) not null,
        rate_limit integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table asset_assignments (
        asset_id bigint not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (asset_id, user_id)
    )

create table assets (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        asset_tag varchar(50) not null,
        brand varchar(100),
        condition_rating enum ('BROKEN','EXCELLENT','FAIR','GOOD','POOR') not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        location varchar(100),
        model varchar(100),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance date,
        notes TEXT,
        purchase_date date,
        purchase_price numeric(10,2),
        serial_number varchar(100),
        status enum ('ASSIGNED','AVAILABLE','DAMAGED','IN_MAINTENANCE','LOST','RETIRED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        warranty_expiry date,
        category_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table categories (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        color_code varchar(50),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        icon varchar(50),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        sort_order integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table invoices (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        amount_due numeric(10,2),
        amount_paid numeric(10,2),
        billing_reason varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        currency varchar(255),
        due_date timestamp(6),
        hosted_invoice_url varchar(255),
        invoice_pdf_url varchar(255),
        paid_at timestamp(6),
        period_end timestamp(6),
        period_start timestamp(6),
        status enum ('DRAFT','OPEN','PAID','UNCOLLECTIBLE','VOID') not null,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_invoice_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_subscription_id varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table maintenance_records (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        completed_date date,
        cost numeric(10,2),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT not null,
        downtime_hours integer,
        maintenance_date date not null,
        maintenance_type varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance_date date,
        notes TEXT,
        parts_used TEXT,
        performed_by varchar(100),
        priority enum ('CRITICAL','HIGH','LOW','MEDIUM','URGENT') not null,
        status enum ('CANCELLED','COMPLETED','IN_PROGRESS','OVERDUE','SCHEDULED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        asset_id bigint not null,
        created_by_user_id bigint,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table payment_methods (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        billing_email varchar(255),
        billing_name varchar(255),
        card_brand varchar(255),
        card_exp_month integer,
        card_exp_year integer,
        card_last4 varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        is_default boolean,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_payment_method_id varchar(255) not null,
        type varchar(255) not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table api_keys (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description varchar(500),
        expires_at timestamp(6),
        key_hash varchar(64) not null,
        last_used_at timestamp(6),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        prefix varchar(16) not null,
        rate_limit integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table asset_assignments (
        asset_id bigint not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (asset_id, user_id)
    )

create table assets (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        asset_tag varchar(50) not null,
        brand varchar(100),
        condition_rating enum ('BROKEN','EXCELLENT','FAIR','GOOD','POOR') not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        location varchar(100),
        model varchar(100),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance date,
        notes TEXT,
        purchase_date date,
        purchase_price numeric(10,2),
        serial_number varchar(100),
        status enum ('ASSIGNED','AVAILABLE','DAMAGED','IN_MAINTENANCE','LOST','RETIRED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        warranty_expiry date,
        category_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table categories (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        color_code varchar(50),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        icon varchar(50),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        sort_order integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table invoices (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        amount_due numeric(10,2),
        amount_paid numeric(10,2),
        billing_reason varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        currency varchar(255),
        due_date timestamp(6),
        hosted_invoice_url varchar(255),
        invoice_pdf_url varchar(255),
        paid_at timestamp(6),
        period_end timestamp(6),
        period_start timestamp(6),
        status enum ('DRAFT','OPEN','PAID','UNCOLLECTIBLE','VOID') not null,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_invoice_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_subscription_id varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table maintenance_records (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        completed_date date,
        cost numeric(10,2),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT not null,
        downtime_hours integer,
        maintenance_date date not null,
        maintenance_type varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance_date date,
        notes TEXT,
        parts_used TEXT,

create table api_keys (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description varchar(500),
        expires_at timestamp(6),
        key_hash varchar(64) not null,
        last_used_at timestamp(6),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        prefix varchar(16) not null,
        rate_limit integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table asset_assignments (
        asset_id bigint not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (asset_id, user_id)
    )

create table assets (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        asset_tag varchar(50) not null,
        brand varchar(100),
        condition_rating enum ('BROKEN','EXCELLENT','FAIR','GOOD','POOR') not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        location varchar(100),
        model varchar(100),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance date,
        notes TEXT,
        purchase_date date,
        purchase_price numeric(10,2),
        serial_number varchar(100),
        status enum ('ASSIGNED','AVAILABLE','DAMAGED','IN_MAINTENANCE','LOST','RETIRED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        warranty_expiry date,
        category_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table categories (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        color_code varchar(50),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        icon varchar(50),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        sort_order integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table invoices (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        amount_due numeric(10,2),
        amount_paid numeric(10,2),
        billing_reason varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        currency varchar(255),
        due_date timestamp(6),
        hosted_invoice_url varchar(255),
        invoice_pdf_url varchar(255),
        paid_at timestamp(6),
        period_end timestamp(6),
        period_start timestamp(6),
        status enum ('DRAFT','OPEN','PAID','UNCOLLECTIBLE','VOID') not null,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_invoice_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_subscription_id varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table maintenance_records (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        completed_date date,
        cost numeric(10,2),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT not null,
        downtime_hours integer,
        maintenance_date date not null,
        maintenance_type varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance_date date,
        notes TEXT,
        parts_used TEXT,
        performed_by varchar(100),
        priority enum ('CRITICAL','HIGH','LOW','MEDIUM','URGENT') not null,
        status enum ('CANCELLED','COMPLETED','IN_PROGRESS','OVERDUE','SCHEDULED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        asset_id bigint not null,
        created_by_user_id bigint,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table payment_methods (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        billing_email varchar(255),
        billing_name varchar(255),
        card_brand varchar(255),
        card_exp_month integer,
        card_exp_year integer,
        card_last4 varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        is_default boolean,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_payment_method_id varchar(255) not null,
        type varchar(255) not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table refresh_tokens (
        id uuid not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) with time zone not null,
        expires_at timestamp(6) with time zone not null,
        ip_address varchar(64),
        replaced_by varchar(255),
        revoked_at timestamp(6) with time zone,
        token_hash varchar(64) not null,
        user_agent varchar(255),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table report_schedules (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        day_of_month integer,
        day_of_week integer,
        enabled boolean not null,
        filters jsonb,
        format enum ('CSV','PDF') not null,
        frequency enum ('DAILY','MONTHLY','WEEKLY') not null,
        include_charts boolean,
        last_run_at timestamp(6),
        next_run_at timestamp(6),
        recipient_emails varchar(255) array,

create table api_keys (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description varchar(500),
        expires_at timestamp(6),
        key_hash varchar(64) not null,
        last_used_at timestamp(6),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        prefix varchar(16) not null,
        rate_limit integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table asset_assignments (
        asset_id bigint not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (asset_id, user_id)
    )

create table assets (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        asset_tag varchar(50) not null,
        brand varchar(100),
        condition_rating enum ('BROKEN','EXCELLENT','FAIR','GOOD','POOR') not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        location varchar(100),
        model varchar(100),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance date,
        notes TEXT,
        purchase_date date,
        purchase_price numeric(10,2),
        serial_number varchar(100),
        status enum ('ASSIGNED','AVAILABLE','DAMAGED','IN_MAINTENANCE','LOST','RETIRED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        warranty_expiry date,
        category_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table categories (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        color_code varchar(50),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        icon varchar(50),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        sort_order integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

        tenant_id bigint not null,

        amount_paid numeric(10,2),

        due_date timestamp(6),

        stripe_invoice_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_subscription_id varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table api_keys (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description varchar(500),
        expires_at timestamp(6),
        key_hash varchar(64) not null,
        last_used_at timestamp(6),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        prefix varchar(16) not null,
        rate_limit integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table asset_assignments (
        asset_id bigint not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        primary key (asset_id, user_id)
    )

create table assets (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        asset_tag varchar(50) not null,
        brand varchar(100),
        condition_rating enum ('BROKEN','EXCELLENT','FAIR','GOOD','POOR') not null,
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        location varchar(100),
        model varchar(100),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance date,
        notes TEXT,
        purchase_date date,
        purchase_price numeric(10,2),
        serial_number varchar(100),
        status enum ('ASSIGNED','AVAILABLE','DAMAGED','IN_MAINTENANCE','LOST','RETIRED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        warranty_expiry date,
        category_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table categories (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        active boolean not null,
        color_code varchar(50),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT,
        icon varchar(50),
        name varchar(100) not null,
        sort_order integer,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table invoices (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        amount_due numeric(10,2),
        amount_paid numeric(10,2),
        billing_reason varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        currency varchar(255),
        due_date timestamp(6),
        hosted_invoice_url varchar(255),
        invoice_pdf_url varchar(255),
        paid_at timestamp(6),
        period_end timestamp(6),
        period_start timestamp(6),
        status enum ('DRAFT','OPEN','PAID','UNCOLLECTIBLE','VOID') not null,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_invoice_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_subscription_id varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table maintenance_records (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        completed_date date,
        cost numeric(10,2),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        description TEXT not null,
        downtime_hours integer,
        maintenance_date date not null,
        maintenance_type varchar(100) not null,
        next_maintenance_date date,
        notes TEXT,
        parts_used TEXT,
        performed_by varchar(100),
        priority enum ('CRITICAL','HIGH','LOW','MEDIUM','URGENT') not null,
        status enum ('CANCELLED','COMPLETED','IN_PROGRESS','OVERDUE','SCHEDULED') not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        vendor varchar(100),
        asset_id bigint not null,
        created_by_user_id bigint,
        primary key (id)
    )

create table payment_methods (
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        tenant_id bigint not null,
        billing_email varchar(255),
        billing_name varchar(255),
        card_brand varchar(255),
        card_exp_month integer,
        card_exp_year integer,
        card_last4 varchar(255),
        created_at timestamp(6) not null,
        is_default boolean,
        stripe_customer_id varchar(255) not null,
        stripe_payment_method_id varchar(255) not null,
        type varchar(255) not null,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        primary key (id)
    )

create table refresh_tokens (

        user_id bigint not null,
